JOHANNESBURG - The SABC is inviting the public to nominate suitable candidates to be appointed as non-executive members of its board. The public broadcaster has opened nominations for eight candidates who are qualified and have a deep commitment to strengthening the SABC's mandate of informing the public. Parliament's portfolio committee on communications said the closing date for nominations is 6 August. "This is your chance to contribute to building a SABC that is credible, independent and sustainable," said national coordinator Uyanda Siyotula. This public call is an opportunity for you to nominate good people to join the SABC Board. Have your say and have your way! #SABCBoardNominations pic.twitter.com/83D75NV9US 